.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-VALIDATE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.24" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-validate \- Validate a compose spec without submitting a job
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose validate [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Parse, normalize, and validate the compose specification without touching cluster state or submitting a Slurm job.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--strict\-env\fR
Fail when ${VAR:\-default} or ${VAR\-default} fallbacks are used because VAR is missing.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose validate \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose validate \-f compose.yaml \-\-strict\-env
hpc\-compose validate \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
